<div class="entrycontent">Now you get to hear them making noise <i>constantly</i>, with the bonus of advertisements.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.mbta.com/about_the_mbta/news_events/?id=13647&month=&year">http://www.mbta.com/about_the_mbta/news<wbr />_events/?id=13647&month=&year</a><br /><br />"in case you were wondering how riding the T could be made less tolerable"<br /><br />There is a feedback form, please use it:  <a href="http://www.mbta.com/riding_the_t/feedback/">http://www.mbta.com/riding_the_t/feedba<wbr />ck/</a><br /><br />I just did:<blockquote>Please cancel this T-Radio thing.  There is enough noise, and this will only make me more miserable when I'm around it, and less likely to take public transportation.&lt;/a&gt;</blockquote></div>

